From Brian Dealy CSC Subject Re Encyclopedia Directory of Widgets The Only directory I know of that lists commercial and non commercial widgets is the ICS Widget Data ICS sells the widgets for various There are also some public domain widgets in the The ICS Widget databook is a subscription kind of thing where you pay some nominal fee get a cd with the widgets and then you can use the public domain widgets freely and selectively activate widgets which you want to purchase the right to use from The nice thing about this is that you can purchase whole sets of widgets such as those used in I dont know there pricing schemes but It is often better to buy than to redevelop the more complex widgets especially if you only one customer to distribute This is the extent that I know about them except that I got their databook catalog and it looked impressive lots o' widgets there I dont work for ICS or have any widgets being sold by hope this helps Brian Dealy It not knowing where it's at that's important it's knowing uunet dftsrv kong dealy where it's not Brian Dealy It not knowing where it's at that's important it's knowing uunet dftsrv kong dealy where it's not